<br>
Shield Smash<br>
Breaks target's shield (if they have one).  Effectively removes the shield from your target for 30 seconds.<br>
<br>
Death Nail<br>
30 min timer, does 50% of your remaining hits in damage to your target, and 100% damage to you (i.e. killing you).  So if you have 100 hits left, you take 100 damage opponent takes 50 damage.  If you have 2k hits left, you die but do 1k damage.  Kind of a self sacrifice for the group, probably do your damage first so no rps for you etc...<br>
<br>
Break Arm<br>
Opponent starts taking damage every time he attacks (because his arm hurts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  Needs to be substantially more than a bleed, like 60 damage an attack, the opponent has the option to stop attacking.<br>
<br>
Break Leg<br>
Opponent starts taking damage every time he moves (since his leg hurts  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  Again 60 damage if they move each 3 seconds or so, they can stop if it get's bad <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Impale<br>
Mercenary stabs opponent in chest leaving weapon there.  Opponent takes large initial damage and very large bleed damage for 10 seconds, during this 10 seconds Mercenary can no longer attack (he has no weapon)<br>
<br>
Point Blank Arrow<br>
Very short range archery shot which does huge damage, possibly negating AF completely due to range.  Easily interrupted since range is short etc...<br>
<br>
Poison Arrow<br>
Speaks for itself<br>
<br>
Trap<br>
Bit like a rune, set a trap up somewhere that damages opponents that get close<br>
<br>
Charge<br>
A real charge which will actually move you 500 units in the blink of an eye<br>
<br>
Hostage<br>
PB ability, while mercenary remains still and is not under attack, opponent cannot do anything (as if mezzed), opponent taking damage interrupts the effect.<br>
<br>
Whirling blades<br>
Mercenary forgoes attacks to concentrate on defense.  Mercenary parries every melee attack (+arrows), for 30 seconds, aimed at him.  The engage of parry<br>
<br>
Deflect<br>
For 30 seconds the Mercenary deflects attacks aimed at him, to his target (who cannot be the same attacker), kind of a reverse intercept.  e.g. You attack a caster a tank comes in to help the caster, you deflect the tanks attacks towards his own caster.  Obviously damage would be greatly reduced.<br>
<br>
Throw<br>
PB attack, target is thrown through the air.  Moves target x number of units away from mercenary and drops them for say 10% damage.  Distance thrown is dependant on target's strength<br>
<br>
Engage/Grapple<br>
PB attack, forces you to become your target's target <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   That is for x seconds the only thing your opponent can target is you, you have them engaged in combat.  Broken if target gets out of range<br>
<br>
Split attack<br>
For x seconds your mainhand will hit your target, but your offhand will swing at another random target within range.  100% chance to swing but offhand will NOT hit your target if no other target is close enough.<br>
<br>
Slip Target<br>
Kind of an instant stealth/unstealth, automatically removes you from anyone's target window<br>
<br>
True Ignore Pain<br>
No damage for x seconds, after this time all damage is then calculated (so you're probably dead <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
True Avoidance of Magic<br>
For next x seconds, a total of x spells are automatically resisted.  e.g. effect lasts 30 seconds and will auto resist next 3 spells.<br>
<br>
Fake Death<br>
You appear to die, opponents get an already killed message no rps etc... but then in x seconds you come back to life.<br>
<br>
Offhand Attack<br>
Your offhand attack get's style bonuses for x seconds<br>
<br>
Charging attack<br>
The mercenary is automatically forced into a sprint, uses endurance, but doesn't need endurance to work.  The mercenary cannot stop moving but if he gets a successful hit on anyone it is considered a charge attack and the damage is multiplied by a significant factor<br>
<br>
Just some ideas to throw around, not saying any of them are viable but I want something 'unique'.<br>
<br>
